<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - FULLER 10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS - INSTALL - INPUT BEARING
        COVER
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="1">
        <title>INPUT BEARING COVER</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f13032f6">Figure 156.</hotlnk>
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tap the input shaft and bearing rearward to seat the bearing snap ring against the case.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Slide a new gasket and the input bearing cover over the input shaft. Make sure the oil
                return hole in the cover and gasket is aligned with the hole in the front of the case.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply Loctite 242 or equivalent to the bolt threads, and install the six (6) bolts. Tighten
                the bolts to 54 to 61 Nm (40 to 45 ft-lbs).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13032f6" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg13/G13032F6.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 156. Input Bearing Cover Assembly</caption>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
